-- Bahrain Looks to Invest in German Family Companies, FT Deutschland Reports
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2010-10-27T05:21:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-27/bahrain-looks-to-invest-in-german-family-companies-ft-deutschland-reports.html
Bahrain is in talks with several
German family-owned companies as it looks for investment
opportunities in stable and technologically leading businesses,
the  Financial Times Deutschland  reported, citing Shaikh Mohammed bin Essa Al Khalifa , who heads the country’s economic
development board.  The Gulf country is interested in smaller and medium-sized
companies in the automotive industry and other areas, the
newspaper said. Shaikh Mohammed didn’t mention any names or a
specific investment volume, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Cornelius Rahn  in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
